The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                               The City Diary
                Two Kali puja pandals were damaged by fire on Monday. At one of the pandals, located on Fern Road near Gariahat, two tenders fought the flames for 20 minutes. Fire officials said a part of the idol was also damaged. The cause of the blaze could not be ascertained. The other pandal that caught fire was in Burrabazar. Three tenders doused the fire, said firemen. A preliminary probe suggested a short-circuit might have caused the fire. The fire department is probing whether there was any lapse on the part of the organisers.    A family from Chetla was robbed of jewellery, clothes and cash worth Rs 50,000 while returning from Uttar Pradesh on the Down Bag Express on Sunday night. The family lodged a complaint with the GRP at Howrah station at 12.30pm on Monday. GRP sources said Sajjad Ali, 28, had boarded the train at Gonda station on Sunday afternoon with his wife, mother and child. They discovered the theft after the train reached Barauni in Bihar.    A couple were seriously injured after the motorcycle they were riding skidded off Diamond Harbour Road on Monday afternoon. According to police, Mohammad Akbar and Alia from Kidderpore were heading towards Behala when the mishap occurred. A bus hit Alia after she fell off the bike and her condition was critical, said an officer. The couple were admitted to CMRI Hospital.     A fire broke out in a firecracker godown in Mahestala, on the southern fringes of the city, on Monday, injuring three persons, including the godown owner. Police said the trio were admitted to SSKM Hospital.     The Bangladeshi minister for forest and environment, Hasan Mehmood Chowdhury, called on chief minister at Calcutta Information Centre on Monday. Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee said they spoke about preservation of forests and the environment.    Officials of Chinese airline Air China visited the city on Monday to conduct a feasibility study for starting operations between Calcutta and Chenghdu in China.                                                                                                                                                                   
